  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add the <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with<strong> half </strong>the <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the <strong>tin foil</strong> around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the corn is tender – this is your <strong>smoky corn</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice the<strong> red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir until dissolved</p><p>Once dissolved, add the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>sliced red chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and set aside – this is your<strong> quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the<strong> black beans</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in 75ml<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ultimate vegan burger patties</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and put in the oven for 10-12 min or until almost cooked through</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained black beans</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and the <strong>remaining smoked paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your<strong> black bean chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>ciabattas</strong> in half</p><p>Wash the gem lettuce, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Remove 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>leaves</strong> from the<strong> gem lettuce </strong>and set aside, then cut the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the patties are almost cooked through, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>ciabatta halves</strong>, cut side up</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 3-4 min or until the ciabatta halves are hot and crusty</p><p>Slice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>slices</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-plant-based-chilli-burger-with-smoky-corn/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fill each <strong>warmed ciabatta</strong> with a <strong>lettuce leaf, </strong>2 <strong>tomato slices </strong>and a<strong> vegan patty </strong>and top with the <strong>black</strong> <strong>bean chilli </strong>and the<strong> quick-pickled chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Serve the <strong>smoky corn</strong> and<strong> lettuce wedges</strong> to the side and drizzle some of the <strong>pickling liquid</strong> over the lettuce</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
